<paragraph id="8A7536860D6CFFBEFF313180FC49FB6F" blockId="19.[151,1437,1226,1424]" box="[151,932,1226,1251]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFF313180FF4FFB6F" bold="true" box="[151,162,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">*</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4DCA4D050D6CFFBEFF043180FDBCFB6F" authority="(Poey 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Poey" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[162,593,1226,1251]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Rhizoprionodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porosus">
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFF043180FE2DFB6E" bold="true" box="[162,448,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Rhizoprionodon porosus</emphasis>
(Poey 1861)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFDF73180FD80FB6F" bold="true" box="[593,621,1226,1251]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">—</emphasis>
Caribbean Sharpnose Shark
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2D0650D0D6CFFBEFF6F31A7FCE4FAA4" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="8A7536860D6CFFBEFF6F31A7FCE4FAA4" blockId="19.[151,1437,1226,1424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Justification: Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EE5B4B770D6CFFBEFE7A31A7FD23FA8A" author="Clavijo, I. E. &amp; Yntema, J. A. &amp; Ogden, J. C." box="[476,718,1261,1286]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref71351" refString="Clavijo, I. E., Yntema, J. A. &amp; Ogden, J. C. (1980) An annotated list of the fishes of St. Croix, U. S. Virgin Islands. West Indies Lab, Special Publication, 2 nd Ed., 1 - 49." type="book chapter" year="1980">
Clavijo 
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFD9C31A4FD9AFA8A" box="[570,631,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
did not list this species, it undoubtedly occurs in St. Croix. 
<bibRefCitation id="EE5B4B770D6CFFBEFF6D3045FE81FAA4" author="Randall, J. E." box="[203,364,1295,1320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref80326" refString="Randall, J. E. (1968) Caribbean reef fishes, 1 st Ed. T. F. H. Publications, Jersey City, New Jersey, 318 pp." type="book" year="1968">Randall (1968</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4) documented it from 
<collectingRegion id="480EF8640D6CFFBEFD013045FCE8FAA4" box="[679,773,1295,1320]" country="United States Virgin Islands" name="Saint John" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">St. John</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2D0650D0D6CFFBEFF6F3078FBECFAC7" box="[201,1025,1330,1355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8A7536860D6CFFBEFF6F3078FBECFAC7" blockId="19.[151,1437,1226,1424]" box="[201,1025,1330,1355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Distribution: 
<bibRefCitation id="EE5B4B770D6CFFBEFEF93078FDD4FAC7" author="Compagno, L. J. V." box="[351,569,1330,1355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="251 - 655" refId="ref71831" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984 b) Sharks of the world: an annotated and illustrated catalogue of shark species known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, 4 (2), 251 - 655." type="journal article" year="1984">Compagno (1984b)</bibRefCitation>
WA (BA, GA, 
<collectionCode id="ECDBAE430D6CFFBEFD4E3079FCE5FAC6" box="[744,776,1331,1354]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">VI</collectionCode>
, LA, 
<collectionCode id="ECDBAE430D6CFFBEFCE13078FC9AFAC7" box="[839,887,1330,1355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">WC</collectionCode>
, nSA, sSA).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2D0650D0D6CFFBEFF6F301FFD0DFA74" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8A7536860D6CFFBEFF6F301FFD51FA1C" blockId="19.[151,1437,1226,1424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Remarks: Campagno (1984b) stated that 
<taxonomicName id="4DCA4D050D6CFFBEFD33301CFCE0FAE1" baseAuthorityName="Poey" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[661,781,1366,1389]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Rhizoprionodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porosus">
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFD33301CFD4BFAE1" box="[661,678,1366,1389]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFD13301CFCE0FAE1" box="[693,781,1366,1389]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">porosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found close inshore on insular shelves of the Caribbean and is one of the commonest inshore sharks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A7536860D6CFFBEFF313095FD0DFA74" blockId="19.[151,736,1503,1528]" box="[151,736,1503,1528]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B8BEEA940D6CFFBEFF313095FD8CFA74" bold="true" box="[151,609,1503,1528]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4DCA4D050D6CFFBEFF313095FEBCFA74" box="[151,337,1503,1528]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">SPHYRNIDAE</taxonomicName>
—hammerhead sharks
</emphasis>
(2 species)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
